The paper deals with developing a fast and memory-efficient algorithm for causal discovery from high-dimensional datasets. This involves the use of parallel computing techniques to optimize the PC algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves the use of statistical inference and information theory, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with computational aspects of the algorithm, which makes cs.IT (Information Theory) another possible sub-category.
